Analyzing the testimonies given by Ihmus (Testimonies 0 to 5), he describes a sequence where he was flying a paraglider, encountered gale force winds, had to make an emergency landing at the Inner Sanctum, and suffered a head injury causing memory loss.

Looking at the evidence, particularly Evidence 11 (Mountain Range Poster), it shows the Inner Sanctum is located at 2310 meters and to the east, and Mt. Poniponi is 2298 meters and to the west. Ihmus claims (Testimony 1) that just as Mt. Poniponi was drawing near, something terrible happened (wind?), and he had to make an emergency landing at the Inner Sanctum, which lies in the opposite direction. Given their relative positions (Inner Sanctum east, Mt. Poniponi west), it seems contradictory that he was approaching Mt. Poniponi and then landed at the Inner Sanctum nearby. The two locations are in different directions. This suggests a contradiction between Testimony 1 and Evidence 11.

